{{Refimprove|date=May 2010}} {{ infobox football tournament | current = [[2017–18 Brunei FA Cup]] | logo = | founded = | number of teams = | region = {{flag|Brunei}} | current champions = [[Indera SC]] (2017–18) | most successful team = [[MS ABDB]] (7 titles) }} The '''Brunei FA Cup''' or '''DST FA Cup''' for sponsorship reasons is [[Brunei]]'s premier knockout tournament in men's [[football (soccer)]].<ref>{{cite web |title=National Football Association of Brunei Darussalam|url=https://www.dst.com.bn/dst-corporate-social-responsibility/football/national-football-association-of-brunei-darussalam/|date=|publisher=Data Stream Technologies, Brunei Darussalam|accessdate=3 February 2017}}</ref> The current format is administered by the [[National Football Association of Brunei Darussalam]] (NFABD) since 2012.<ref>{{cite web |title=FOOTBALL/ DST BRUNEI FA CUP FA Cup kick off moved to June 10 |url=http://msabdbft.blogspot.com/2012/06/football-dst-brunei-fa-cup-fa-cup-kick.html|date=1 June 2012|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=3 February 2017}}</ref>
The championship winner will receive B$7,000 ($5,000 USD) as prize money.
==Participating== All football clubs that have registered with the NFABD are eligible to enter the FA Cup, including non-league teams such as [[FC Phosphor]] who have entered every edition of the competition despite having not played league football since 2013.<ref>{{cite web |title=FC Phosphor return to Brunei football scene|url=http://msabdbft.blogspot.com/2014/07/fc-phosphor-return-to-brunei-football.html|date=3 July 2014|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=3 February 2017}}</ref>
Due to more stringent regulations, the 2017 edition onwards will only feature 20 clubs, the majority coming from the [[2017 Brunei Super League|Super League]] and [[2017 Brunei Premier League|Premier League]].
*2012 = 44 teams<ref>{{cite web |title=44 teams to clash for Brunei FA Cup |url=http://msabdbft.blogspot.com/2012/06/44-teams-to-clash-for-brunei-fa-cup.html|date=7 June 2012|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=3 February 2017}}</ref> *2014/15 = 36 teams<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nfabd.org/schedules/dst.htm|title=PIALA FA - DST 2014 Schedules|publisher=National Football Association of Brunei Darussalam|date=|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170203162610/http://nfabd.org/schedules/dst.htm|archivedate=3 February 2017|accessdate=20 November 2017}}</ref> *2015 = 28 teams<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nfabd.org/schedules/dst-fa-cup-teams.htm|title=DST FA Cup 2015|publisher=National Football Association of Brunei Darussalam|date=|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170203162608/http://nfabd.org/schedules/dst-fa-cup-teams.htm|archivedate=3 February 2017|accessdate=20 November 2017}}</ref> *2016 = 28 teams<ref>{{cite web |title=DST FA Cup 2016|url=http://nfabd.org/schedules/dst-fa-2016-teams.htm|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170203162458/http://nfabd.org/schedules/dst-fa-2016-teams.htm|archivedate=3 February 2017|accessdate=20 November 2017}}</ref> *2017 = 20 teams<ref>{{cite web |title=DST FA CUP 2017|url=http://www.nfabd.org/schedules/dst-fa-cup-schedules.htm|date=6 November 2017|publisher=National Football Association of Brunei Darussalam|accessdate=20 November 2017}}</ref>
==Previous winners== Winners so far are:<ref>{{cite web|title=Brunei - List of Cup Finals|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/bruneicuphist.html|publisher=RSSSF|accessdate=26 August 2011}}</ref> ;FA Cup ([[Football Association of Brunei Darussalam|BAFA]]-administered) *2002 : '''[[Wijaya FC]]''' 1-0 [[Royal Brunei Armed Forces Sports Council|MS ABDB]] *2003 : '''[[Royal Brunei Armed Forces Sports Council|MS ABDB]]''' 3-0 [[Kota Ranger]] *2004 : '''[[DPMM FC]]''' 0-0 [[Royal Brunei Armed Forces Sports Council|MS ABDB]] [aet, 3-1 pen] *2005/06 : '''[[AH United]]''' 2-2 [[Royal Brunei Armed Forces Sports Council|MS ABDB]] [aet, 4-3 pen] *2006/07 : ''not held'' *2007/08 : '''[[Royal Brunei Armed Forces Sports Council|MS ABDB]]''' 1-0 [[Wijaya FC]] *2008/09 : ''not held'' *2009/10 : '''[[Royal Brunei Armed Forces Sports Council|MS ABDB]]''' 2-1 [[QAF FC]] ;DST FA Cup (NFABD-administered) *2012 : '''[[Royal Brunei Armed Forces Sports Council|MS ABDB]]''' 1-0 [[Indera FC]] [aet] *2013 : ''not held'' *2014/15 : '''[[Royal Brunei Armed Forces Sports Council|MS ABDB]]''' 2-0 [[Najip FC]] *2015 : '''[[Royal Brunei Armed Forces Sports Council|MS ABDB]]''' 3-2 [[Indera SC]] *2016 : '''[[Royal Brunei Armed Forces Sports Council|MS ABDB]]''' 1-0 [[Najip I-Team]] *[[2017–18 Brunei FA Cup|2017/18]] : '''[[Indera SC]]''' 2-0 [[MS PDB]]
