{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = KR-völlur | nickname = | image =KR-völlur Main Stand.jpg | image_size =300px | location = [[Reykjavík]], [[Iceland]] | broke_ground = | opened = 1951 | renovated = | owner = | operator = | construction cost = | architect = | tenants = [[Knattspyrnufélag Reykjavíkur|KR Reykjavík]] | seating_capacity = 2,781 (1,541 seated) }}
'''KR-völlur''' is a football [[stadium]] in [[Reykjavík]], [[Iceland]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xu25x4WuFwIC|title=Iceland|last=Parnell|first=Fran|last2=O'Carroll|first2=Etain|date=2007-01-01|publisher=Lonely Planet|isbn=9781741045376|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=x5na1WdCYywC|title=:The Definitive Guide Featuring All the Facts and Figures from the FIFA World Cup|last=Oliver|first=Guy|date=2006-01-01|publisher=Headline Book Publishing|isbn=9780755315062|language=en}}</ref>
It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and has been the home stadium of [[Knattspyrnufélag Reykjavíkur]] since 1984. The stadium holds about 2,700 people and is located at the Kaplaskjólsvegur in West Reykjavík.
==Stats== *Size: 105 x 68 m *Opening game: July 18, 1951 [[Knattspyrnufélag Reykjavíkur|KR]] - [[Vålerenga Fotball|Vålerenga]] 3 - 2 *Record attendance: September 26, 1998 - 5400 [[Knattspyrnufélag Reykjavíkur|KR]] - [[ÍBV]] *Average attendance 2007 season: 1873 people
