{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Lugogo Stadium | nickname = Lugogo Cricket Oval | country = Uganda | image = | location = [[Kampala]], [[Uganda]] | establishment = 1957 | seating_capacity = 10,000 | end1 = | end2 = n/a | year1 = 1957–present | club1 = [[Uganda national cricket team|Uganda]] | date = August 14, | year = 2014 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/28/1748.html Ground profile }}
'''Lugogo Stadium''', also known as '''Lugogo Cricket Oval''', is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Kampala]], [[Uganda]]. The first recorded match held on the ground came in 1957 when Kenya Asians played Sunder Cricket Club.
In that same year [[Uganda national cricket team|Uganda]] first used the ground when the national team played the Sunder Cricket Club.<ref name="OTH">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/28/1748_misc.html|title=Other matches played on Lugogo Stadium|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=18 October 2011}}</ref> The ground held its inaugural [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match when an [[East African Invitation XI cricket team|East African Invitation XI]] played the touring [[Marylebone Cricket Club]] in 1963.
A further first-class match followed in 1967 when a combined [[East Africa cricket team|East Africa]] team played the touring [[India national cricket team|Indians]]. The next first-class matches to be held on the ground didn't come until 2005, when Uganda played two matches there in the [[2005 ICC Intercontinental Cup|Intercontinental Cup]] against [[Kenya national cricket team|Kenya]] and [[Namibia national cricket team|Namibia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/28/1748_f.html|title=First-Class Matches played on Lugogo Stadium|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=18 October 2011}}</ref> The Lugogo Stadium is the only cricket venue in Uganda to have held first-class cricket.
Surrounding the cricket ground there are [[tennis courts]] and a [[association football|football]] ground which is the home ground of [[Kampala City Council FC]].
