{{Infobox football biography | name = Said Al-Sobakhi | image = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1985|06|20|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Rafah]], [[State of Palestine|Palestine]] | height = | currentclub = [[Tarji Wadi Al-Nes|Wadi Al-Nes]] | clubnumber = 8 | position = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]] | clubs1 = [[Khadamat Rafah]] | clubs2 = [[Tarji Wadi Al-Nes|Wadi Al-Nes]] | years1 = –2008 | years2 = 2008– | caps1 = | caps2 = 21 | goals1 = | goals2 = 17 | nationalyears1 = 2008– | nationalteam1 = [[Palestine national football team|Palestine]] | nationalcaps1 = 7 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | pcupdate = | ntupdate = }}
'''Said Al-Sobakhi''' ({{lang-ar|سعيد السباخي}}; born 20 June 1985) is a [[Palestinian people|Palestinian]] [[Association football|footballer]] who plays his club football for [[Tarji Wadi Al-Nes|Wadi Al-Nes]]. He plays primarily as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]], although he can be deployed as an [[Attacking midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]].
==Club career== In October 2008, Al-Sobakhi moved from his Gaza-based club [[Khadamat Rafah]] to [[West Bank Premier League]] club [[Tarji Wadi Al-Nes|Wadi Al-Nes]]. His first season proved to a very successful one, his 17 league goals meant placed him second in the scorers charts and helped earn Wadi Al-Nes the league title.
==International career== Al-Sobakhi made his national team debut for Palestine during the [[2008 West Asian Football Federation Championship|2008 WAFF Championship]]. During [[2010 AFC Challenge Cup qualification|2010 AFC Challenge Cup qualifying]], Al-Sobakhi made his first start for the national team where he scored his first goal in a 1–1 draw with [[Kyrgyzstan national football team|Kyrgyzstan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maannews.net/arb/ViewDetails.aspx?ID=152809|title=After a 1-1 draw, Palestine say goodbye to Challenge Cup, whilst Kyrgyzstan advances |publisher= Ma'an News Agency|date=2009-03-30|language=Arabic}}</ref>
